IlunyaBrowser — Linux installation
==================================

Arch Linux (yay)
----------------
From the repository root:

  chmod +x packaging/arch/install-yay.sh
  ./packaging/arch/install-yay.sh

Or manually:

  yay -S ./packaging/arch

After publishing to AUR:

  yay -S ilunyabrowser


Debian / Ubuntu
---------------
Install build dependencies:

  sudo apt install build-essential debhelper python3-pyqt6 python3-pyqt6.qtwebengine

Build and install:

  chmod +x packaging/debian/build-deb.sh
  ./packaging/debian/build-deb.sh
  sudo apt install ../ilunyabrowser_1.0.0-1_all.deb


Fedora / RHEL / Rocky / AlmaLinux
---------------------------------
Install build dependencies:

  sudo dnf install rpm-build python3-pyqt6 python3-pyqt6-webengine

Build and install:

  chmod +x packaging/rpm/build-rpm.sh
  ./packaging/rpm/build-rpm.sh
  sudo dnf install packaging/rpmbuild/RPMS/noarch/ilunyabrowser-*.rpm


Gentoo
------
Prepare a local overlay:

  chmod +x packaging/gentoo/prepare-overlay.sh
  ./packaging/gentoo/prepare-overlay.sh

Then:

  sudo eselect repository add ilunyabrowser packaging/gentoo-overlay/ilunyabrowser
  sudo emerge --sync ilunyabrowser
  sudo emerge -av www-client/ilunyabrowser


Run
---
  ilunyabrowser

Or find IlunyaBrowser in the application menu.
